cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as it deals with a metric for comparing the citation capacity of pairs of journals. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves analyzing citation distributions. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the comparison of journals based on citation patterns. It may also fall under cs.CY (Computational Geometry) as it involves analyzing the shape of citation distributions. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it involves the development of a new metric for comparing journals.
